                <h2 id="keyboardPanelTitle">âŒ¨ï¸ Keyboard Tricks</h2>
                <div class="info-text">
                    <p>System Shortcuts:
â€¢ Access Spotlight Search: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Space bar.
â€¢ Return to the Home screen: Press Command (âŒ˜) + H.
â€¢ Show the Dock: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Option (âŒ¥) + D.
â€¢ Show the App Library: Press Shift (â‡§) + Globe + A.
â€¢ Open Quick Note: Press Globe + Q.
â€¢ Open Siri: Press Globe + S.
â€¢ Open Control Center: Press Globe + C.
â€¢ Open Notification Center: Press Globe + N.
â€¢ Show all windows: Press Globe + Down Arrow.
â€¢ Open the App Switcher: Press Globe + Up Arrow.

Multitasking Shortcuts:
â€¢ Switch to the last active app: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Tab.
â€¢ View all active apps: Press and hold Command (âŒ˜) + Tab.
â€¢ Open Split View: Press Control (âŒƒ) + Globe + Left Arrow to move an app to the left, or Control (âŒƒ) + Globe + Right Arrow to move it to the right.
â€¢ Switch the position of apps in Split View: Press Control (âŒƒ) + Globe + Left or Right Arrow.
â€¢ Open Slide Over: Press Globe + Backslash.
â€¢ Move the Slide Over window: Press Option (âŒ¥) + Globe + Left or Right Arrow.

Safari and App-Specific Shortcuts:
â€¢ Take a full-screen screenshot: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Shift + 3.
â€¢ Take a screenshot and enter markup immediately: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Shift + 4.
â€¢ Open a new private tab: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Shift + N.
â€¢ Open a new tab: Press Command (âŒ˜) + T or Command (âŒ˜) + N.
â€¢ Close the current tab: Press Command (âŒ˜) + W.
â€¢ Close all tabs in Tab Grid: Press Shift + Command (âŒ˜) + W.
â€¢ Go to the next tab: Press Option (âŒ¥) + Command (âŒ˜) + Right Arrow, or Control (âŒƒ) + Tab, or Command (âŒ˜) + }.
â€¢ Go to the previous tab: Press Option (âŒ¥) + Command (âŒ˜) + Left Arrow, or Shift + Control (âŒƒ) + Tab, or Command (âŒ˜) + {.
â€¢ Reopen the last closed tab: Press Shift + Command (âŒ˜) + T.
â€¢ Go to a specific tab (1-8): Press Command (âŒ˜) + (1-8).
â€¢ Go to the last tab: Press Command (âŒ˜) + 9.
â€¢ Open the Tab Grid: Press Shift + Command (âŒ˜) + .
â€¢ Open a new Incognito tab: Press Shift + Command (âŒ˜) + N.
â€¢ Open a new Incognito window: Press Option (âŒ¥) + Shift + Command (âŒ˜) + N.
â€¢ Open a new window: Press Option (âŒ¥) + Command (âŒ˜) + N.

General Navigation and Text Editing:
â€¢ Navigate between elements in an app (like fields, lists, buttons): Press Tab.
â€¢ Select all text: Press Command (âŒ˜) + A.
â€¢ Copy selected text: Press Command (âŒ˜) + C.
â€¢ Cut selected text: Press Command (âŒ˜) + X.
â€¢ Paste copied text: Press Command (âŒ˜) + V.
â€¢ Undo the last action: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Z.
â€¢ Redo the last undone action: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Shift + Z.
â€¢ Jump to the top of a page: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Up Arrow.
â€¢ Jump to the bottom of a page: Press Command (âŒ˜) + Down Arrow.
â€¢ Highlight text one character at a time: Press Shift + Left or Right Arrow.
To view all available shortcuts for the specific app you are using, press and hold the Command (âŒ˜) key. For a complete list of system-wide shortcuts, press and hold the Globe key on a compatible keyboard.</p>
